29
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:18,510
The cause of death was blood loss
from a gunshot wound to the abdomen.

30
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:23,410
We believe the weapon was this shotgun
found on the floor near the body.

31
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,180
I see.

32
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:30,020
The victim was shot while
sleeping on the sofa.

33
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:37,150
The windows of this study face north, so the
lights were kept on even during the daytime.

34
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:41,250
A room doesn't get sunlight
with north-facing windows.

35
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:46,280
According to forensics, the estimated
time of death is around noon.

36
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:51,750
He was shot with that shotgun, right?

37
00:03:51,930 --> 00:03:55,250
Most likely, since it was
left on the floor there.

38
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,880
Let's review the case.

39
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:03,210
While Tawake was sleeping on the
sofa, the culprit entered the room,

40
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:07,970
killed him with a shotgun, dropped the
murder weapon, and fled the scene.

41
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,010
Is that right?

42
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:14,960
Most likely. Since the glass door in
the living room was partially open,

43
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:17,610
we believe the culprit entered
and exited through there.

44
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,610
Take the body away for an autopsy.

45
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:27,240
We found no signs that the culprit searched
the room, so we don't believe they were a thief.

46
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:29,400
Could the motive have been hatred?

47
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,620
What's this?

48
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:37,550
It's a bloodstain.

49
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:39,950
This must've splattered
here when he was shot.

50
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:45,130
But since there's no blood on the curtains,
that means they were open then, right?

51
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:48,260
Did the culprit take the time to close them?

52
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,730
If that's the case, then
why did they do that?

53
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:58,370
They were probably trying to
delay the discovery of the body.

54
00:04:58,370 --> 00:05:00,730
It would give them more time to get away.

55
00:05:00,950 --> 00:05:04,110
But who'd be looking in through this window?

56
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:04,900
Huh?

57
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:07,880
Isn't it visible from the next house over?

58
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:10,370
What's up with that house?

59
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:15,000
The weather's so nice, but
all the shutters are closed.

60
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:21,270
Apparently the neighbors moved away
last week. It's currently unoccupied.

61
00:05:21,270 --> 00:05:22,630
It's empty, huh?

62
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:23,940
Inspector.

63
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,090
There's blood on this as well,

64
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:30,600
but there isn't a drop on
the floor or wall around it.

65
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:35,730
Was that stand located
elsewhere during the murder

66
00:05:35,730 --> 00:05:38,480
and moved afterwards by the culprit?

67
00:05:38,930 --> 00:05:40,980
Why would that be necessary?

68
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:45,610
Inspector Megure, I'm back from
questioning the neighbors.

69
00:05:46,130 --> 00:05:49,250
Nobody saw any suspicious persons.

70
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,050
Also, in the neighborhood...

71
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:55,110
There wasn't anyone who heard a gunshot.

72
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:59,960
I'm not surprised no one heard
anything with this racket.

73
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:04,130
The body was discovered by
Tawake's apprentices, right?

74
00:06:04,130 --> 00:06:06,050
We're having them wait in the living room.

75
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:09,910
Tawake Shintaro had apprentices, huh?

76
